{"id":473034,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_B._Oakley","text":"Robert Bigger Oakley (March 12, 1931 \u2013 December 10, 2014) is an American diplomat. He was a Foreign Service Officer. He was United States Ambassador to Zaire, Somalia, and Pakistan. In the early 1990s, he was a special envoy during the American involvement in Somalia under the Jimmy Carter, Ronald Reagan, and George Bush presidencies.\nOakley died in McLean, Virginia from complications from Parkinson's disease, aged 83.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":64},{"uri":"Diplomat","surface_form":"diplomat","offset":73},{"uri":"Foreign_Service_Officer","surface_form":"Foreign Service Officer","offset":92},{"uri":"United_States_Ambassador","surface_form":"United States Ambassador","offset":124},{"uri":"Zaire","surface_form":"Zaire","offset":152},{"uri":"Somalia","surface_form":"Somalia","offset":159},{"uri":"Pakistan","surface_form":"Pakistan","offset":172},{"uri":"Unified_Task_Force","surface_form":"American involvement in Somalia","offset":236},{"uri":"Jimmy_Carter","surface_form":"Jimmy Carter","offset":278},{"uri":"Ronald_Reagan","surface_form":"Ronald Reagan","offset":292},{"uri":"George_H._W._Bush","surface_form":"George Bush","offset":311},{"uri":"McLean%2C_Virginia","surface_form":"McLean, Virginia","offset":352},{"uri":"Parkinson%27s_disease","surface_form":"Parkinson's disease","offset":393}]}